 and other aspects of culture|location=Chicago|publisher=University of Chicago Press|ref=harv}}\n* {{Citation |jstor = 43102168|title = The Sapir-Whorf Hypothesis: A Preliminary History and a Bibliographical Essay|journal = Journal of Linguistic Anthropology|volume = 2|issue = 2|pages = 173\u2013198|last1 = Koerner|first1 = E. F. Konrad|year = 1992|doi = 10.1525/jlin.1992.2.2.173}}\n* {{citation|last=Lakoff|first=George|authorlink=George Lakoff|year=1987|title=Women, fire, and dangerous things|publisher=University of Chicago Press}}\n* {{citation|last=Leavitt|first=John|year=2011|title=Linguistic Relativities: Language Diversity and Modern Thought|publisher=Cambridge University Press|location=Cambridge, UK | isbn = 978-0-521-76782-8 | ref = harv }}\n* {{cite book|first=Penny |last=Lee|title=The Whorf Theory Complex: A Critical Reconstruction|url={{google books |plainurl=y |id=GZnlaURrZYkC}}|date=1 January 1996|publisher=John Benjamins Publishing|isbn=978-90-272-4569-4|ref=harv}}\n* {{citation|last=Lenneberg |first=Eric|authorlink=Eric Lenneberg|first2=A. M. |last2=Brown|year=1956|title=The Language of Experience: a Study in Methodology|journal=Indiana University Publications in Anthropology and Linguistics}}\n* {{citation|last=Lenneberg |first=Eric|authorlink=Eric Lenneberg|year=1953|title=Cognition in Ethnolinguistics|journal=Language|volume=29|issue=4|pages=463\u2013471|doi=10.2307/409956|jstor=409956}}\n* {{citation|last=Levinson |first=Stephen C.|authorlink=Stephen C. Levinson|title=Language and Space|year=1996|journal=Annual Review of Anthropology|volume=25|pages=353\u201382|doi=10.1146/annurev.anthro.25.1.353|url=https://semanticscholar.org/paper/f31ae448cdedf05807f008a2a6cd81fbee60a7a1}}\n* {{citation |jstor = 640692|title = Studying Spatial Conceptualization across Cultures: Anthropology and Cognitive Science|journal = Ethos|volume = 26|issue = 1|pages = 7\u201324|last1 = Levinson|first1 = Stephen C.|year = 1998|doi = 10.1525/eth.1998.26.1.7|hdl = 11858/00-0