 Rise by 100 Percent or More|last=Otterson|first=Joe|date=December 3, 2018|work=[[Variety (magazine)|Variety]]|accessdate=December 3, 2018}}</ref>\n\n| title8    = [[#ep18|Crash and Burn]]\n| date8     = March 7, 2019\n| rs8       = 0.9/4\n| viewers8  = 5.24<ref name=\"2.08\"/>\n| dvr8      = 0.7\n| dvrv8     = 2.54\n| total8    = 1.6\n| totalv8   = 7.78<ref>{{cite web|url=https://programminginsider.com/live7-weekly-ratings-the-blacklist-tops-broadcast-telecasts-in-adults-18-49-percentage-gains/|title=Live+7 Weekly Ratings: 'The Blacklist' Tops Broadcast Telecasts in Adults 18\u201349 Percentage Gains|last=Pucci|first=Douglas|date=March 20, 2019|work=Programming Insider|accessdate=March 20, 2019}}</ref>\n\n| title9    = [[#ep19|I Fought the Law]]\n| date9     = March 14, 2019\n| rs9       = 0.8/4\n| viewers9  = 5.02<ref name=\"2.09\"/>\n| dvr9      = 0.6\n| dvrv9     = 2.34\n| total9    = 1.4\n| totalv9   = 7.30<ref>{{cite web|url=https://programminginsider.com/live7-weekly-ratings-the-passage-on-fox-concludes-its-season-with-modest-gains/|title=Live+7 Weekly Ratings: 'The Passage' on Fox Concludes its Season with Modest Gains|last=Pucci|first=Douglas|date=March 26, 2019|work=Programming Insider|accessdate=March 26, 2019}}</ref>\n\n| title10   = [[#ep20|Crazy Train]]\n| date10    = March 21, 2019\n| rs10      = 0.9/4\n| viewers10 = 5.55<ref name=\"2.10\"/>\n| dvr10     = 0.6\n| dvrv10    = 2.27\n| total10   = 1.5\n| totalv10  = 7.82<ref>{{cite web|url=https://programminginsider.com/live7-weekly-ratings-the-orville-on-fox-leads-broadcast-network-telecasts-in-percentage-gains-among-adults-18-49/|title=Live+7 Weekly Ratings: 'The Orville' on Fox Leads Broadcast Network Telecasts in Percentage Gains Among Adults 18\u201349|last=Pucci|first=Douglas|date=April 2, 2019|work=Programming Insider|accessdate=April 2, 2019}}</ref>\n\n| title11   = [[#ep21|Baby Boom]]\n| date11    = March 28, 2019\n| rs11      = 1.0/5\n| viewers11 = 5.44<ref name=\"2.11\"/>\n| dvr11     = 0.6\n|