haracter -Fix a typo in one click", "url_page": "//en.wikipedia.org/wiki/The_Scholar_Who_Walks_the_Night"}
{"title_page": "Thaha Municipality", "text_new": "{{Infobox settlement\n<!--See the table at Infobox settlement for all fields and descriptions of usage-->\n<!-- Basic info  -->| name                            = Thaha Municipality\n| native_name                     = \u0925\u093e\u0939\u093e \u0928\u0917\u0930\u092a\u093e\u0932\u093f\u0915\u093e\n| other_name                      = Palung\n| settlement_type                 = [[Municipality]]\n| image_skyline                   = \n| image_caption                   = \n| image_flag                      = \n| image_seal                      = \n| nickname                        = Daman Palung\n| motto                           = <!-- images and maps  -->\n| image_map                       = \n| mapsize                         = \n| map_caption                     = \n| pushpin_map                     = Nepal\n| pushpin_label_position          = bottom\n| pushpin_mapsize                 = 300\n| pushpin_map_caption             = Location of Thaha Municipality in Nepal\n<!-- Location -->| coordinates                     = {{coord|27|36|N|85|05|E|region:NP_type:city|display=inline,title}}\n| subdivision_type                = Country\n| subdivision_name                = {{flag|Nepal}}\n| subdivision_type1               = Province\n| subdivision_type2               = [[Districts of Nepal|District]]\n| subdivision_name1               = [[Bagmati Pradesh]]\n| subdivision_name2               = [[Makwanpur District]]\n| established_title               = Established\n| established_date                = 18 May 2014\n<!-- Area    -->| government_footnotes            = \n| government_type                 = [[Mayor\u2013council government|Mayor\u2013council]]\n| leader_title                    = [[Mayor]]\n| leader_name                     = Lab Sher Bista\n| leader_title1                   = [[Deputy Mayor]]\n| leader_name1                    = Khadga Gopali\n| unit_pref                       = <!--Enter: Imperial, if Imperial (metric) is desired-->\n| area_footnotes                  = \n| area_total_km2                  = <!-- ALL fields dealing with a measurements are subject to automatic unit conversion-->\n<!-- Population   -->| elevation_footnotes             = <!--for references: use <ref> </ref> tags-->\n| elevation_m                     = <!-- Area/postal codes & others -->\n| population_total                = 41623\n| population_as_of                = 2011\n| population_footnotes            = \n| population_density_km2          = auto\n| population_blank1_title         = Ethnicities\n<!-- General information  -->| population_note                 = \n| postal_code_type                = Postal Code\n| postal_code                     = 44110\n| area_code                       = 057\n| website                         = http://www.thahamun.gov.np\n| footnotes                       = |<!-- Politics -->\n| timezone                        = [[Nepal Standard Time|NST]]\n| utc_offset                      = +5:45\n| timezone_DST                    = \n| utc_offset_DST                  = \n| blank_name                      = \n| blank_info                      = \n| official_name                   = \n}}\n\nPopularly known as Daman or Palung or Tistung - Palung, '''Thaha Municipality (\u0925\u093e\u0939\u093e \u0928\u0917\u0930\u092a\u093e\u0932\u093f\u0915\u093e)''' is a municipality in [[Makwanpur District]] of [[Bagmati Pradesh]] in mid [[Nepal]].In Nepali Thaha (\u0925\u093e\u0939\u093e) means to know. It was one of the biggest communist political movement led by hon. Rupchandra Bista(Ru Da Ne). He started the Thaha Movement. And Thaha Municipality is dedicated to his contributions to this region.\n\nIt is one of the most beautiful tourist destination and best place to live in Bagmati Pradesh. The climate here is so mild. It's never too hot in summer nor too cold in winter. You still can't sleep without a blanket even in summer. Winter is a little bit cold here causing the water to freeze and some snowfall too, usually in the upper hills of the valley. There is no snowfall in the valley since 2063 B.S. The municipality was established on 18 May 2014 merging the existing [[Palung]], [[Daman, Nepal|Daman]] and [[Bajrabarahi]] village development committees. On new [[Constitution of Nepal]],  there is provision of one state, 7 provinces and 744 local bodies. Thaha municipality is one local body out of 10 in Makwanpur district, formed by merging existing Thaha municipality, [[Tistung VDC]], [[Chitlang VDC]] and [[Aagra VDC]]. This municipality is divided in to 12 wards to facilitate in administrative and development activities.<ref>[http://www.myrepublica.com/portal/index.php?action=news_details&news_id=74336 72 new municipalities announced] My Republica </ref><ref>[http://www.ekantipur.com/the-kathmandu-post/2014/05/08/news/govt-announces-72-new-municipalities/262559.html Govt announces 72 new municipalities] The Kathmandu Post </ref>\n\nMain occupation of people living here is agriculture. They are one of the major exporters of potato and other vegetables (cauliflower, cabbage, brinjal, raddish and different varieties of green chillies including capsicum) to big cities like Kathmandu, Hetauda, Narayangadh, Pokhara, Birgunj and even to India. Vegetable cultivation started only after 2050 B.S. Before that people used to cultivate rice, wheat, millet, barley, etc. But now vegetable cultivation have changed the lifestyle of whole valley. It's very hard to see rice, wheat cultivation anymore. Everyone is just busy making money by selling vegetables.\n\nShikharkot, Thana Bazzar, Bagekhola, Okhar Bazzar, Phant Bazzar and Khalte Bazzar are the major gathering and market place in Thaha Nagar Palika.\n\n==References==\n<references />\n\n{{Makwanpur District}}\n\n[[Category:Populated places in Makwanpur District]]\n[[Category:Municipalities in Bagmati Pradesh]]\n[[Category:Nepal municipalities established in 2014]]\n\n\n{{Bagmati-geo-stub}}\n", "text_old": "{{Info